The paper proposes a framework for dynamic network visualization, which involves creating regularized graph layouts. This falls under the category of graph drawing and network visualization, which is covered by cs.GR. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of preserving the mental map between layouts of consecutive time steps, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of grouping and temporal penalties, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper applies the proposed framework to several data sets, which could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI) or data mining (cs.SD).
